Ne7 9. Ne1 Nd7 10. Be3 f5 11. f3 f4 12. Bf2 g5 13. Nd3
{ 13.Rc1  comes into consideration. } 13... Nf6 14. c5 Rf7 15. Rc1 Ng6 16. cxd6
{ A reasonable alternative can be found in  16.Kh1  . } 16... cxd6 17. Nb5 g4
18. Qb3 { That's already the losing move.  18.fxg4  Nxe4  19.Bf3  Ng5∞  . }
