Bxg3 Nh5
{ This pawn sacrifice is standard and very powerful, as the black pieces get plenty of play on the dark squares. The bishop will be moved to h6, the queen to g5 and the knights are drawn to the square f4. White's main weakness is the g-pawn, which can additionally be attacked by Rg7. }
21. Bh2 { 21.Be1  a6  22.Qa3  Bf8-+ } 21... Bh6 22. Rc2 a6 23. Nc3
