1. d4 g6 2. c4 Bg7 3. Nc3 d6 4. e4 e5 5. Nf3 Nd7 6. Be2 Ne7 7. O-O O-O 8. d5 h6
9. b4
{ That's a bad version of the Bayonet Attack, with Black being two tempi up. Nevertheless, White should be slightly better here. }
9... f5 10. a4 f4 11. Ba3 { 11.h3  g5  12.Nh2⩲ } 11... g5 12. Nd2
{ 12.h3  Nf6  13.Nh2⩲ } 12... Nf6 13. c5 g4 14. f3
{ Obviously, White misjudges the situation and is dreaming of building a fortress.  14.b5  Ng6  15.g3∞  . }
14... g3
{ The only choice White has is, whether to lose on dark squares or on the light squares. }
15. h3 { A loss on the light squares it is. } 15... Ng6
{ This is stronger than the immediate  15...Bxh3  , which is also feasible. }
16. Re1 Nh4 17. Bf1 Nh7
{ White is unable to stop Black from annihilating his kingside structure. } 18.
cxd6 cxd6 19. Nc4
{ Obviously, this weakens the point f3. Let's check an alternative line.   19.b5  Ng5  20.Rc1  Rf6  21.Kh1   21.Re2  Qe8  22.b6  Qh5  23.Nb5  Bxh3  24.gxh3  Nhxf3+  25.Nxf3  Nxf3+  26.Kh1  Ng5-+  Rg6  22.Re2   22.Qe2  Nxh3  23.gxh3  g2+-+  Nxg2  23.Bxg2  Nxh3  24.Bxh3  Bxh3-+ }
19... Rf7
{ Black doesn't have to hurry, as White's problem isn't time, but space. He simply cannot organize a defensive setup.   19...Bxh3!?  20.gxh3  Rc8-+ }
20. b5 Bf8 21. Ra2 Ng5 22. Ree2 Ngxf3+
{ 22...Nxh3+!  would have been quicker, but who really cares?  23.gxh3  Nxf3+  24.Kh1  Qh4  25.Nd2  Ng5  26.Rh2  f3-+ }
23. gxf3 Nxf3+ 24. Kg2 Ng5
{ 24...Bxh3+!  is the fastest lane to victory. Here just one pretty line:  25.Kxh3  Qh4+  26.Kg2  Qh2+  27.Kxf3  Qh1+  28.Rg2  Qh5  . }
25. Rec2 Bxh3+ 26. Kg1 Rc8 27. Bxh3 Nxh3+ 28. Kg2 Qh4 29. Nd2 Nf2 30. Qg1 Qh3+
31. Kf3 Qg4+ 32. Kg2 f3+
{ These two on the 3rd rank is a reliable sign, that something has gone terribly wrong for White. }
33. Kf1 Nh3 *

