18... Bxe5 19. Qxh5 Bxa1 20. Rxa1 Ng6 21. Bc3
{ Who wouldn't think that this bishop is at least worth a rook. That already leaves us with an extra-pawn, apart from the other benefits of our position. If you are interested, you can now have a look at how this might play out. }
21... Bd7 22. f4 { Fixing both, the weak f-pawn and the miserable knight. }
22... Re8 23. Bd3 Qe7 24. Bd4 Rea8 25. Bc2 c6 26. dxc6 Bxc6 27. Kf2
{ Chess is a team game. Every piece has to contribute to the best of its ability. }
27... Re8 28. Nc3 Ra5 29. Bb3 Qf7 30. Rb1
{ Renewing the threat of pushing the c-pawn. } *

