{ Apparently, White's pieces don't mind this small material loss at all. } 23.
Qc2 e4
{ 23...Ra8  24.Nc3  Rf8  25.a5  White has ample play against Black's weaknesses specifically  the pawns on b7 and f5, which is powered by the fact that Black's pieces lack proper coordination. }
24. f3 e3 25. Bc3 f4
{ Black has to prevent f3-f4. After  25...Bxc3  26.Qxc3  Kh7  27.f4  ,  the e3-pawn will soon be history, Black suffers from weak pawns on f5, d6, and b7. }
26. Bh3 { White is winning the exchange. } *

