[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5
Ne7 9. b4 c5 { This leads directly to a positionally lost position for Black. }
10. bxc5 dxc5 11. a4
{ The idea is simple, White will attack Black's c-pawn. If it gets defended by b6, the pawn break a4-a5 will turn this move into a lethal weakness. }
11... a5
{ Let's see what happens if Black does not stop the a-pawn thrust.   11...Ne8  12.Be3  b6  13.a5  Rb8  14.axb6Ν  axb6  15.Qb3±  threatening Bxc5 and intending to step up the pressure on the b-pawn with Na4 and Rfb1. }
12. Rb1 Ne8 13. Ne1 f5 14. Qb3
{ With the clear route for the Knight to go to d3 to pressure the c5-pawn. }
14... Ra6 15. Nd3 b6 16. f4
{ Black's pieces are in no position to cope with this central breakthrough. }
16... fxe4 { 16...exf4?  17.e5± } 17. Nxe5 Nd6 18. Nb5 Ra8 19. Bb2 *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
