[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "9... Bg4"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5
Ne7 9. b4 Bg4
{ While it is true that this bishop is mostly short of squares, exchanging it for the knight without compensation is a mistake, as this surrenders the light squares. }
10. Be3
{ The bishop is hardly seen on this square, as it would normally provoke ...Ng4 which is clearly unavailable here. }
10... Nh5
{ 10...Nd7  11.c5  Bxf3  Black has to surrender his bishop.   11...f5  is refuted by  12.Ng5  .  12.Bxf3  f5  13.c6Ν  bxc6  14.dxc6  Nf6  15.b5±  Realizing the queenside majority will be the way to victory. }
11. c5 Nf4 12. Nd2 { 12.h3  is also good. } 12... Nxe2+ 13. Nxe2 Bc8
{ 13...Bd7  does not help matters as  14.Nc4  puts pressure on the d6-pawn. }
14. Nc3 f5 15. f3
{ White might already be winning, as Black will have problems with his d-pawn. }
