17... a5 18. Rc1 axb4 { 18...Nf5  19.b5+- } 19. Qd4+ Kg8 20. Qxb4 Nf5
{ From the knight's perspective, this is a decent square. In a global sense, however, interrupting the connection between rook and f-pawn cannot be embraced. }
