14... h5 15. a4 f5
{ Of course, omitting ...f7-f5 on move 13 doesn't mean that it cannot be played later on. In this case, however, it is linked to a completely unsound knight sacrifice. }
16. cxd6 cxd6
{ 1-0 @@StartBracket@@31@@EndBracket@@ Savina,A @@StartBracket@@2202@@EndBracket@@ -Severiukhina,Z  @@StartBracket@@2199@@EndBracket@@ St Petersburg 2008. }
17. g3
{ This doesn't oblige you to take the knight on the very next move. You might as well prepare the capture or combine the threat of capturing it with other ideas. }
17... g4 18. Nb5 Rf6 { 18...fxe4  19.Nbxd6+- } 19. gxf4
{ That's a good moment. } 19... a6 { 19...Nh4  20.Ra3  Nf3+  21.Rxf3+- } 20.
