{ 19...bxa5  20.c5  Nf6  21.Nxf6  Bxf6  22.Ng5  a4  23.Ne4  Bg7  24.Bb4+-  when Black's central structure collapses. }
20. Nfg5 Nxe4 21. Bxe4 bxa5 22. h4 { White goes directly after the king. }
22... Qe8 23. h5 Bh6 24. hxg6 Bxg5 25. Qh5 { Not  25.Bxg5?  Bf5  . } 25... Nxg6
26. Qxg5 Bd7 27. Qh5 a4 28. Ree3
{ White's idea is to penetrate on the dark squares. Instead of presenting a whole thicket of lines, I will give but one example: }
28... Kg8 29. Rf3
{ White has a winning attack.   29.Rf3  Rxf3  30.Rxf3  a3  31.Rf6  a2  32.Bxg6  a1=Q+  33.Kg2  Bh3+  34.Kh2□  Qxg6  35.Rxg6+  hxg6  36.Qxg6+  Kh8  37.Bg5  Rf8  38.Bf6+  Rxf6  39.Qxf6+  Kg8  40.Qg6+  Kf8  41.Qh6+  Kf7  42.Qh7+  Ke8  43.Qxh3  with a won queen ending. }
