18... Bxe5 19. Qxh5 Bxa1 20. Rxa1 Ng6 21. Bc3
{ Who wouldn't think that this bishop is at least worth a rook. That already leaves us with an extra-pawn, apart from the other benefits of our position. If you are interested, you can now have a look at how this might play out.   21.Bc3  Bd7   21...Qe7  22.Re1  Qf7  23.Qg5  23...f4  24.g4  Rxa4  25.h4  f3  Hoping for 26.h5? Qf4.  26.Re4+-  22.f4!  Fixing both, the weak f-pawn and the miserable knight.  22...Re8  23.Bd3  Qe7   23...Re3  24.Qd1!  Stronger than 24.Bxf5.  24...Ra8  25.Qd2  Re8  26.Qf2  The queen has interesting options from here.  26...Rc8  27.Nd4!  Rf8  28.Qc2  Ne7  29.Re1  Qe8  30.Bb2  30...Qf7  31.Ne6  h6  32.g4+-  Black's castle is a draughty place.  24.Bd4  Rea8  25.Bc2  c6  26.dxc6  Bxc6  27.Kf2  Chess is a team game. Every piece has to contribute to the best of its ability.  27...Re8   27...Be4  28.Bb3  Kf8  29.Qh6+  Ke8  30.h4+-  28.Nc3  Ra5   28...Be4  29.Bxe4  fxe4  30.Nd5+-   28...Qf7  29.Qxf5  Qxf5  30.Bxf5+-  followed by Nb5.  29.Bb3  29...Qf7  30.Rb1  Renewing the threat of pushing the c-pawn. Now, Black's rook has to be used as a blockader.  30...Rc5  31.h4  White is using every single man.  31...Re6  32.Qg5  Kf8  33.Bxc5  dxc5  34.Rd1+-  . }
