13. Nd2 { White stabilizes the center, before proceeding on the queenside. }
13... c6 { This is a better moment for this move than it was on move 12. } 14.
Bf1 Kh7 15. Ra2
{ The rook leaves a potentially dangerous diagonal and gets ready for activities on the second rank. }
15... Rf7
{ 15...Bd7?  16.a6  White gains access to the square d5.  16...b6  17.dxc6  Nxc6  18.b5  Nd4  19.Nb3  Be6  20.Rd2±  Here comes the rook! 1-0 @@StartBracket@@38@@EndBracket@@ Moreto Quintana,A @@StartBracket@@2286@@EndBracket@@-Esposito,L @@StartBracket@@2446@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2017. }
16. h3 Rb8 17. Ba3 cxd5 { It's difficult to wait forever. } 18. exd5
{ Obviously, White's majority is further advanced than Black's.  18.cxd5  is equally good. }
18... b6 19. axb6 axb6 20. Nb5 Ra8 21. Qa1 g5 22. c5
{ 22.Bb2  , in order to penetrate down the a-file is a reasonable alternative. }
22... dxc5 23. d6 Ng6 24. bxc5 bxc5 25. Bxc5
{ The passed d-pawn gives White good practical chances. ½-½ @@StartBracket@@48@@EndBracket@@ Pravec,L @@StartBracket@@2384@@EndBracket@@ -De Bari,V @@StartBracket@@2440@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2017. }
