exf5
{ This is a better practical approach than  14.Bd2  , which was played in ½-½ @@StartBracket@@36@@EndBracket@@ Gonzaga Grego, L @@StartBracket@@2402@@EndBracket@@-Zugrav, W @@StartBracket@@2577@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2017. The game continued  14...h6  15.Ne6  Bxe6  16.dxe6  fxe4  , when things can become very complicated, with Black targeting the f-pawn. }
