17. Ra3 Qe7 18. Nb5
{ Now, Black has to reckon with the little maneuver Bxf5, followed by Nd4-e6. }
18... Ne8 19. h3
{ As Black can't do much, these semi-waiting moves are pretty strong. The advance g2-g4 could become an option in some line down the road and air for the king is always a good-to-have. }
19... Bd7 20. Be4
{ As Black's bishop stands now in the way between queen and c-pawn, White doesn't have to fear ...Nf6 anymore. That's one of the virtues of a semi-waiting move. }
20... Bh6 21. Qc1 Kh8 22. f4
{ White can also play it slow with  22.g3  followed by h4 and Bg2. } 22... Bxb5
{ Black has to take some pressure off his position. } 23. cxb5 Bxg5 24. fxg5
Neg7 25. g4 Nd4 26. Kg2
{ The knight g7 is nicely dominated by both of White's g-pawns. } *

