{ 22...f4  23.Rxe5+- } 23. Bd2 Ra6 24. Bb4 Ne7
{ 24...Rf6  25.Rxe5  Raxe6  26.Rxe6  Rxe6  27.Qxf5+-  loses a pawn. } 25. Rxe5
Bxe5 26. Qxh6+ Kg8 27. Qg5+ Bg7 28. Rg3 Ng6 29. Qxg6 Qf6 30. Bc3
{ This is a good example for the influence of the e-pawn. Here, it inhibits both of Black's rooks. }
*

