10... a5 11. bxa5 Rxa5 12. a4
{ I consider this stronger than the more frequent  12.Nd2  . Leaving the knight  as long as possible on f3, appears like a good general guideline to me. }
12... c5
{ Black's position is very passive and White has a clear plan to make progress. }
13. Ra3 Kh8 14. Nb5 Ng8
{ Black wants to exchange or activate his passive bishop. } 15. Bd2
{ The game 1-0 @@StartBracket@@32@@EndBracket@@ Shariyazdanov, A @@StartBracket@@2612@@EndBracket@@-Dobrov, V @@StartBracket@@2272@@EndBracket@@ Oberwart 2000 saw  15.g3  , instead. }
15... Ra6 16. Qc1 { Preventing Black's idea. } 16... f5
{ Bad, but the only active or critical variation. } 17. exf5 Bxf5
{ 17...gxf5?  18.Nxe5+- } 18. g3 Qd7 19. Ng5 Nhf6 20. Ne6 { Nevertheless. }
20... Rc8 { 20...Bxe6  21.dxe6  Qxe6  22.Nc7+- } 21. Bf3
{ These knights are horrific. Black is paralyzed. } *

