14... Nf6 15. Ng5
{ The knight is targeting the well-known weak spot in the heart of Black's position. }
15... c6 16. Rb3 { The rook is focusing on the b-pawn and the weak square b6. }
16... Ng6 17. Be3 Qe8
{ 17...Ra8?  18.c5!  Opening the a2-g8 diagonal.  18...h6  19.Bc4!  hxg5  20.dxc6+  Kh8  21.cxb7  Bxb7  22.Rxb7+-  Black better makes sure, that White's queen doesn't arrive on the h-file. Then again, it's game over anyways. }
18. Bb6 Ra8 19. dxc6 bxc6 20. Qxd6 Bh6 21. Nh3
{ White is close to winning, as Black has no real compensation for the pawn. }
