24... Qc8
{ 24...Kg8?!  25.c5  Bxc2  26.Qxc2±  Nxd5?  27.Qb3  Actually, White needed the king on g8 to play c5.  27...c6  28.cxd6+-  . }
25. Ra3 Bf4
{ The bishop supports the e-pawn and sometimes enables attacking ideas linked to ...g5-g4. }
26. Rb3
{ The rook is targeting Black's main weakness. Besides this active intention, there is also a prophylactic idea involved. Black's most important idea in this position is to get rid of his weak b-pawn by means of ...Ra6 and ...b6. This can now be prevented by withdrawing the bishop from the b-file. }
