27. Bxf5 gxf5 28. g3
{ 28.c5!?  is also favorable for White, when Black has to answer  28...e4  with a messy position. }
28... Rg8
{ 28...Bh6?  29.Nxe5  dxe5  30.Bxf8  Bxf8  31.Rxe5  Rxa5  32.Rf3+-  Obviously, the rooks enjoy a lot of activity here. }
29. Kh2 Bh6 30. Nh4 { Targeting the soft spot f5. } 30... f4
{ 30...Bg5?  Donating a tempo for White's f-pawn.  31.Ng2  31...Bh6  32.f4  Bg7  33.fxe5  dxe5  34.Nh4+-  Black cannot keep his pawn duo intact.   30...b6?  There is no time for this.  31.Rf3  f4   31...bxa5  32.Bc3  Rg5  33.g4  f4  34.Rxf4+-  32.Bc3  32...Nh5  33.Qd3  bxa5   33...Rf8  34.g4  Ng7  35.Ng6++-  34.Nf5  Bg5  35.c5  Undermining the e-pawn.  35...a4  36.cxd6  cxd6  37.Nxd6  Rxd6  38.Bxe5+  Rf6  39.d6+-  Material losses are inevitable. }
