{ 31...Bg5?  32.Ng2  fxg3+  33.fxg3  Qe8  34.Ref1  Of course, the unstable knight is the problem, here.  34...Qh5   34...Qg6  35.Be1  Overprotecting the g-pawn.  35...b6  36.Rf5  threatening h4.  36...Nd7  37.Qe2  bxa5  38.Nh4  Bxh4  39.gxh4+-  followed by Rf7 and h5. The penetration cannot be avoided anymore.  35.h4  Raa8  36.Qb1  Qh6  37.Be1+-  We can trust the engine in such a position. Here, just one beautiful line:  37...Ng4+  38.Kh3  b6  39.Rf7  bxa5  40.Rxc7  a4  41.Ne3!!  Bxe3  42.Rff7  Nf6  43.Rxf6  Rg6  44.Rff7  44...Rag8  45.Rxh7+  Qxh7  46.Rxh7+  Kxh7  47.h5  etc.   31...b6?  32.Bc3+-  Black cannot parry the threat of gxf4. }
