30. Qxd2 e4
{ If Black stays passive, White won't be short of plans.   30...Kg8?  31.cxd6  cxd6  32.Rb5+- }
31. Qh6 { The delicate situation of Black's king becomes clearly visible. }
31... Raa8
{ 31...Kg8  32.Ng5!  This move has a beautiful point.  32...Qxf2+  33.Kxf2  Ng4+  34.Kg1  Nxh6  At first glance, things appears to be okay for Black, now that the queens have left the board. But White holds a little surprise in store...  35.Ne6  Rc8  The rook has to move into a tactical constellation.   35...Rb8  36.c6  Rxa5  37.Nxc7  Ra7  38.Rxe4+-  36.c6  bxc6  37.Nd4!  cxd5  38.Nc6  Rca8  39.Nxa7  Rxa7  40.Ra1  Ra6  41.Rb7+- }
