{ Improving on ½-½ @@StartBracket@@54@@EndBracket@@ Bromberger, S @@StartBracket@@2345@@EndBracket@@-Shaked, T @@StartBracket@@2500@@EndBracket@@ Groningen 1997, where  20.cxd6  was played. White is switching to direct attack by exchanging the king's personal defender.   As this is a bit difficult to play in practice,  20.Bc3  ,  followed by Qb3 is a good alternative OTB. }
20... Bxd2 21. Qxd2 { Threatening Ng5, followed by Bxf5 and Ne6. } 21... Bxe4
22. Rxe4 dxc5 23. Nxe5
{ With the fall of the e-pawn, the king's shelter stands wide open. Here is one exemplary line. }
23... Rf8 24. Rd1 Nf5 25. Ng4 b6 26. axb6 cxb6 27. h3
{ In many positions its a good idea to fully energize your pieces before dealing the final blow. Now, the rook on d1 doesn't have to watch the first rank anymore. }
27... Nd4 28. Rde1 Ra7 29. Kh1 Qxd5 30. Re7 *

