17... Ndf6
{ Black didn't want to sit still, which is no easy thing to do in chess, and continued with his plan to fight for the e4-square. But as Bobby said 'If you wanna get some @@StartBracket@@squares@@EndBracket@@, you gotta give some.' Now White has free hand with his standard pawn-break. }
18. c5
{ Nothing spectacular has occurred. Black just allowed a losing structure to come into existence, where the fragility of the pawn d6 is more than the position can bear. White's simple plan is to transfer his knight to c4. }
18... fxe4 19. Bxe4
{ That's better than  19.Nxe4  . Now, Black can't alleviate the pressure  by taking on e4, as this would lead to a collapse of his pawn structure after Nxe4. }
19... Bf5
{ This appears to be a bit more active, but it doesn't make a big difference. }
20. Bd3 Bxd3
{ 20...Ne7  21.Bc4  Bf4  22.Qb3+-  White is threatening to uproot Black's position with Nb5 and Qa3. }
