18. Ra3
{ Once more, this is the most active place for the queen's rook. In the game 1-0 @@StartBracket@@56@@EndBracket@@ Farago, I @@StartBracket@@2462@@EndBracket@@-Havasi, G @@StartBracket@@2274@@EndBracket@@ Budapest 2014, White chose  18.Rc1  instead. }
18... Nf5 19. h3
{ A multi-purpose move. White is creating air for his king, waits for information and prepares a potential g2-g4. }
19... Nd4
{ That's not increasing the scope of the King's Indian bishop very much, as it will be looking at its fellow pawn. }
20. Nxd4 exd4 21. Bc2 Bd7 22. c5 Bf5
