21. Nc3 Bd7 22. a6 b6 23. c6
{ Sometimes, it is better to tie Black up completely, than to open the c-file or maintain the pressure against d6. }
23... Bc8 24. Bc2 Ne7 25. Nb5
{ This knight is terrible for Black, as it binds two major pieces. } 25... Bf5
26. Bd1
{ Of course, White doesn't want to exchange a piece, which can hardly move. }
26... Kh8 27. g4 { Now, the bishop is completely dominated by White's pawns. }
27... Bc8 28. Nh4 g5 29. Ng2
{ White will build up a battery on the b1-h7 diagonal and might later penetrate on the light squares. }
