{ Exchanging the often bad King's Indian bishop is always a double-edged sword for Black. In this position, Black has to maintain the pawn on e5 by all means, which strongly reduces his options @@StartBracket@@...dxc5 becomes unappetizing, for instance@@EndBracket@@. White will continue with one of the following plans:    Ng5-e6;  Bf1-g2, Nd2-c4, b4-b5;  f2-f4 at some point. }
